A bug fix for incorrect formula for waitNanos in Clock.java and added tests to verify behaviour of ContentionStrategy backoff methods.

patch by @belliottsmith;

The [Cassandra Jira](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-18097)

Hello everyone,

Importing all classes from a package or static members from a class leads to tight coupling between packages or classes and might lead to problems when a new library version introduces name clashes. This patch intends to fix the issue.

The patch the following commits for a more convenient review process: 

- Update configuration files;
- Update the source code files;

Changes:

- a new rule added to `checkstyle.xml` and `checkstyle_test.xml` configuration files to avoid 'star' imports;
- the `codeStyleSettings.xml` migrated to a new format. This configuration file is deprecated since IntelliJ IDEA 2017.3. All code style settings are located under `<PROJECT_ROOT>/.idea/codeStyles` directory and consist of the following files: `codeStyleConfig.xml`, `Project.xml`;
- the Code style IntelliJ IDEA is updated with `<option name="USE_SINGLE_CLASS_IMPORTS" value="true" />` and `<option name="PACKAGES_TO_USE_IMPORT_ON_DEMAND"><value /></option>` to avoid 'star' imports in IntelliJ IDEA configuration;
- the Import formatting is updated for NetBeans configuration with `auxiliary.org-netbeans-modules-editor-indent.text.x-java.CodeStyle.project.useSingleClassImport=true`;
- there is no dedicated code style configuration for the Eclipse IDE, thus no changes are required here (configurations stored in the `.metadata` directory and located at `eclipse-workspace` that is out of control for the project);
- all `*.java` files are updated to obey the new rule;

A bug fix for 'wait' time to be in nanoseconds for consistency instead of microseconds.

patch by @marianne-manaog, although fix suggested by @belliottsmith;

The [Cassandra Jira](https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-18086)
